+## Local Development with Docker Compose
+
+For local development with all services (PostgreSQL, Traefik, Docker proxy):
+
+```bash
+# From WSL (not Docker Desktop on Windows)
+cp .env.example .env
+# Edit .env with your values (DATABASE_URL, Privy, OpenRouter, etc.)
+
+# Start all services
+docker-compose up -d
+
+# Run database migrations
+docker-compose exec app npx prisma db push
+
+# Seed database
+docker-compose exec app npx prisma db seed
+
+# View logs
+docker-compose logs -f app
+```
+
+### Docker Compose Services
+- **app**: Next.js application (port 3000)
+- **db**: PostgreSQL 16
+- **traefik**: Reverse proxy with automatic HTTPS
+- **docker-proxy**: Secure Docker socket proxy
 
 For the modern chat-centric platform, we recommend Vercel for the frontend/API and Supabase for the PostgreSQL database.
 
